{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are a factual chatbot."}, {"role": "user", "content": "How does the water cycle work?"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "The water cycle describes the continuous movement of water on, above, and below the surface of the Earth. It begins with evaporation, where water from oceans, lakes, and rivers turns into vapor due to the sun's heat. This vapor rises and cools, forming clouds through condensation. Eventually, the water returns to the surface as precipitation, such as rain or snow. Some of this water infiltrates the ground, replenishing groundwater, while the rest flows back into bodies of water, completing the cycle."}]}
